		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in Scala's LazyList that permits code execution during deserialization. This issue could allow an attacker to craft a LazyList containing a malicious Function0 call to execute arbitrary code on a server that deserializes untrusted data. \n            \n            MITIGATION: Users of Scala's LazyList should never permit deserialization of untrusted data.",
